# Comprehensive information criteria demonstration
demonstrate_information_criteria_comprehensive <- function() {
  
  cat("=== COMPREHENSIVE INFORMATION CRITERIA ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  # Generate example data
  set.seed(11111)
  n_persons <- 500
  n_items <- 15
  
  sim_data <- simulate_irt_data_fit(n_persons, n_items, "2PL")
  
  cat("Dataset specifications:\n")
  cat("Persons:", n_persons, "\n")
  cat("Items:", n_items, "\n")
  cat("True model: 2PL\n\n")
  
  # Fit different models
  cat("Fitting multiple models...\n")
  
  models <- list()
  model_results <- data.frame(
    Model = character(),
    LogLik = numeric(),
    Parameters = numeric(),
    AIC = numeric(),
    BIC = numeric(),
    stringsAsFactors = FALSE
  )
  
  # 1PL (Rasch) Model
  tryCatch({
    models$rasch <- mirt(sim_data$data, 1, itemtype = "Rasch", verbose = FALSE)
    
    loglik <- extract.mirt(models$rasch, "logLik")
    n_params <- extract.mirt(models$rasch, "nest")
    aic_val <- extract.mirt(models$rasch, "AIC")
    bic_val <- extract.mirt(models$rasch, "BIC")
    
    model_results <- rbind(model_results, data.frame(
      Model = "1PL (Rasch)",
      LogLik = round(loglik, 2),
      Parameters = n_params,
      AIC = round(aic_val, 2),
      BIC = round(bic_val, 2)
    ))
    
    cat("✓ 1PL model fitted\n")
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("✗ 1PL model failed:", e$message, "\n")
  })
  
  # 2PL Model
  tryCatch({
    models$twopl <- mirt(sim_data$data, 1, itemtype = "2PL", verbose = FALSE)
    
    loglik <- extract.mirt(models$twopl, "logLik")
    n_params <- extract.mirt(models$twopl, "nest")
    aic_val <- extract.mirt(models$twopl, "AIC")
    bic_val <- extract.mirt(models$twopl, "BIC")
    
    model_results <- rbind(model_results, data.frame(
      Model = "2PL",
      LogLik = round(loglik, 2),
      Parameters = n_params,
      AIC = round(aic_val, 2),
      BIC = round(bic_val, 2)
    ))
    
    cat("✓ 2PL model fitted\n")
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("✗ 2PL model failed:", e$message, "\n")
  })
  
  # 3PL Model
  tryCatch({
    models$threepl <- mirt(sim_data$data, 1, itemtype = "3PL", verbose = FALSE)
    
    loglik <- extract.mirt(models$threepl, "logLik")
    n_params <- extract.mirt(models$threepl, "nest")
    aic_val <- extract.mirt(models$threepl, "AIC")
    bic_val <- extract.mirt(models$threepl, "BIC")
    
    model_results <- rbind(model_results, data.frame(
      Model = "3PL",
      LogLik = round(loglik, 2),
      Parameters = n_params,
      AIC = round(aic_val, 2),
      BIC = round(bic_val, 2)
    ))
    
    cat("✓ 3PL model fitted\n")
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("✗ 3PL model failed:", e$message, "\n")
  })
  
  # 4PL Model (if supported)
  tryCatch({
    models$fourpl <- mirt(sim_data$data, 1, itemtype = "4PL", verbose = FALSE)
    
    loglik <- extract.mirt(models$fourpl, "logLik")
    n_params <- extract.mirt(models$fourpl, "nest")
    aic_val <- extract.mirt(models$fourpl, "AIC")
    bic_val <- extract.mirt(models$fourpl, "BIC")
    
    model_results <- rbind(model_results, data.frame(
      Model = "4PL",
      LogLik = round(loglik, 2),
      Parameters = n_params,
      AIC = round(aic_val, 2),
      BIC = round(bic_val, 2)
    ))
    
    cat("✓ 4PL model fitted\n")
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("✗ 4PL model failed:", e$message, "\n")
  })
  
  cat("\n=== MODEL COMPARISON RESULTS ===\n")
  print(model_results)
  
  # Identify best models
  if(nrow(model_results) > 0) {
    best_aic <- model_results[which.min(model_results$AIC), "Model"]
    best_bic <- model_results[which.min(model_results$BIC), "Model"]
    
    cat("\nBest model by AIC:", best_aic, "\n")
    cat("Best model by BIC:", best_bic, "\n\n")
    
    # Calculate AIC and BIC differences
    model_results$AIC_diff <- model_results$AIC - min(model_results$AIC)
    model_results$BIC_diff <- model_results$BIC - min(model_results$BIC)
    
    cat("AIC və BIC fərqləri (minimum modeldən):\n")
    print(model_results[, c("Model", "AIC_diff", "BIC_diff")])
    
    # Interpretation guidelines
    cat("\nInterpretation Guidelines:\n")
    interpretation_guide <- data.frame(
      Evidence_Strength = c("Negligible", "Weak", "Moderate", "Strong", "Very Strong"),
      AIC_BIC_Difference = c("0-2", "2-4", "4-7", "7-10", ">10"),
      Interpretation = c("Models equivalent", "Slight preference", "Clear preference", 
                        "Strong preference", "Decisive preference"),
      Decision_Guidance = c("Use simplest", "Consider parsimony", "Favor better model",
                           "Choose better model", "Strongly favor better model")
    )
    print(interpretation_guide)
    
    # Visual comparison
    if(require(ggplot2, quietly = TRUE)) {
      
      # Prepare data for plotting
      plot_data <- data.frame(
        Model = rep(model_results$Model, 2),
        Value = c(model_results$AIC, model_results$BIC),
        Criterion = rep(c("AIC", "BIC"), each = nrow(model_results))
      )
      
      # Create plot
      p <- ggplot(plot_data, aes(x = Model, y = Value, fill = Criterion)) +
        geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge", alpha = 0.7) +
        scale_fill_manual(values = c("AIC" = "steelblue", "BIC" = "darkred")) +
        labs(title = "Model Comparison: AIC vs BIC",
             x = "Model", y = "Information Criterion Value",
             fill = "Criterion") +
        theme_minimal() +
        theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
              plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 14, face = "bold"))
      
      print(p)
    }
    
    # Detailed model selection recommendation
    cat("\n=== DETAILED MODEL SELECTION ANALYSIS ===\n")
    
    # Calculate evidence weights (Akaike weights)
    aic_weights <- exp(-0.5 * model_results$AIC_diff)
    aic_weights <- aic_weights / sum(aic_weights)
    
    bic_weights <- exp(-0.5 * model_results$BIC_diff)
    bic_weights <- bic_weights / sum(bic_weights)
    
    model_results$AIC_Weight <- round(aic_weights, 3)
    model_results$BIC_Weight <- round(bic_weights, 3)
    
    cat("Model Selection Weights:\n")
    print(model_results[, c("Model", "AIC_Weight", "BIC_Weight")])
    
    cat("\nModel Selection Recommendation:\n")
    
    if(best_aic == best_bic) {
      cat("UNANIMOUS CHOICE: Both AIC and BIC favor", best_aic, "\n")
      cat("Confidence: Very High\n")
      cat("Action: Proceed with", best_aic, "model\n")
    } else {
      aic_diff <- min(model_results$AIC_diff[model_results$Model == best_bic])
      bic_diff <- min(model_results$BIC_diff[model_results$Model == best_aic])
      
      cat("CRITERIA DISAGREEMENT:\n")
      cat("AIC favors:", best_aic, "(BIC difference:", round(bic_diff, 2), ")\n")
      cat("BIC favors:", best_bic, "(AIC difference:", round(aic_diff, 2), ")\n")
      
      if(max(aic_diff, bic_diff) < 4) {
        cat("Decision: CLOSE CALL - Consider practical factors\n")
      } else if(aic_diff > bic_diff) {
        cat("Decision: LEAN TOWARD BIC choice (", best_bic, ") - stronger evidence\n")
      } else {
        cat("Decision: LEAN TOWARD AIC choice (", best_aic, ") - stronger evidence\n")
      }
    }
  }
  
  return(list(
    models = models,
    results = model_results,
    data = sim_data$data
  ))
}

# Run comprehensive information criteria demonstration
ic_comprehensive_demo <- demonstrate_information_criteria_comprehensive()

3 Likelihood Ratio Tests

3.1 Nested Models üçün Statistik Müqayisə

cat("=== LIKELIHOOD RATIO TESTS ===\n\n")
## === LIKELIHOOD RATIO TESTS ===
cat("LRT: Nested modelləri statistik olaraq müqayisə edir\n")
## LRT: Nested modelləri statistik olaraq müqayisə edir
cat("LRT = -2 × (LL_simple - LL_complex)\n")
## LRT = -2 × (LL_simple - LL_complex)
cat("Test statistikası χ² paylanmasına malik (df = difference in parameters)\n\n")
## Test statistikası χ² paylanmasına malik (df = difference in parameters)
# Comprehensive likelihood ratio test demonstration
demonstrate_lrt_comprehensive <- function() {
  
  cat("=== COMPREHENSIVE LRT ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  # Use data from previous demonstration
  if(exists("ic_comprehensive_demo") && !is.null(ic_comprehensive_demo$models)) {
    models <- ic_comprehensive_demo$models
    data_matrix <- ic_comprehensive_demo$data
  } else {
    # Generate new data if needed
    sim_data <- simulate_irt_data_fit(500, 15, "2PL")
    data_matrix <- sim_data$data
    
    # Fit models
    models <- list()
    models$rasch <- mirt(data_matrix, 1, itemtype = "Rasch", verbose = FALSE)
    models$twopl <- mirt(data_matrix, 1, itemtype = "2PL", verbose = FALSE)
    models$threepl <- mirt(data_matrix, 1, itemtype = "3PL", verbose = FALSE)
  }
  
  cat("Available models for LRT:\n")
  cat("Models:", paste(names(models), collapse = ", "), "\n\n")
  
  # Perform LRTs for nested model pairs
  lrt_results <- data.frame(
    Comparison = character(),
    Model_Simple = character(),
    Model_Complex = character(),
    LL_Simple = numeric(),
    LL_Complex = numeric(),
    LRT_Statistic = numeric(),
    df = numeric(),
    p_value = character(),
    Decision = character(),
    Effect_Size = character(),
    stringsAsFactors = FALSE
  )
  
  # 1PL vs 2PL
  if("rasch" %in% names(models) && "twopl" %in% names(models)) {
    
    cat("=== 1PL vs 2PL DETAILED COMPARISON ===\n")
    
    # Extract log-likelihoods
    ll_1pl <- extract.mirt(models$rasch, "logLik")
    ll_2pl <- extract.mirt(models$twopl, "logLik")
    
    # Calculate LRT
    lrt_stat <- -2 * (ll_1pl - ll_2pl)
    
    # Degrees of freedom (difference in number of parameters)
    params_1pl <- extract.mirt(models$rasch, "nest")
    params_2pl <- extract.mirt(models$twopl, "nest")
    df_diff <- params_2pl - params_1pl
    
    # p-value
    p_val <- 1 - pchisq(lrt_stat, df_diff)
    
    # Effect size (pseudo R-squared)
    pseudo_r2 <- (ll_2pl - ll_1pl) / abs(ll_1pl)
    
    # Decision
    decision <- ifelse(p_val < 0.05, "2PL significantly better", "1PL adequate")
    effect_size <- ifelse(pseudo_r2 > 0.02, "Large effect", 
                         ifelse(pseudo_r2 > 0.01, "Medium effect", "Small effect"))
    
    lrt_results <- rbind(lrt_results, data.frame(
      Comparison = "1PL vs 2PL",
      Model_Simple = "1PL (Rasch)",
      Model_Complex = "2PL",
      LL_Simple = round(ll_1pl, 2),
      LL_Complex = round(ll_2pl, 2),
      LRT_Statistic = round(lrt_stat, 3),
      df = df_diff,
      p_value = format(p_val, scientific = TRUE, digits = 3),
      Decision = decision,
      Effect_Size = effect_size
    ))
    
    cat("Detailed Results for 1PL vs 2PL:\n")
    cat("1PL Log-likelihood:", round(ll_1pl, 2), "\n")
    cat("2PL Log-likelihood:", round(ll_2pl, 2), "\n")
    cat("Improvement:", round(ll_2pl - ll_1pl, 2), "\n")
    cat("LRT statistic:", round(lrt_stat, 3), "\n")
    cat("Degrees of freedom:", df_diff, "\n")
    cat("p-value:", format(p_val, scientific = TRUE, digits = 3), "\n")
    cat("Pseudo R-squared:", round(pseudo_r2, 4), "\n")
    cat("Decision:", decision, "\n")
    cat("Effect size:", effect_size, "\n\n")
  }
  
  # 2PL vs 3PL
  if("twopl" %in% names(models) && "threepl" %in% names(models)) {
    
    cat("=== 2PL vs 3PL DETAILED COMPARISON ===\n")
    
    # Extract log-likelihoods
    ll_2pl <- extract.mirt(models$twopl, "logLik")
    ll_3pl <- extract.mirt(models$threepl, "logLik")
    
    # Calculate LRT
    lrt_stat <- -2 * (ll_2pl - ll_3pl)
    
    # Degrees of freedom
    params_2pl <- extract.mirt(models$twopl, "nest")
    params_3pl <- extract.mirt(models$threepl, "nest")
    df_diff <- params_3pl - params_2pl
    
    # p-value
    p_val <- 1 - pchisq(lrt_stat, df_diff)
    
    # Effect size
    pseudo_r2 <- (ll_3pl - ll_2pl) / abs(ll_2pl)
    
    # Decision
    decision <- ifelse(p_val < 0.05, "3PL significantly better", "2PL adequate")
    effect_size <- ifelse(pseudo_r2 > 0.02, "Large effect", 
                         ifelse(pseudo_r2 > 0.01, "Medium effect", "Small effect"))
    
    lrt_results <- rbind(lrt_results, data.frame(
      Comparison = "2PL vs 3PL",
      Model_Simple = "2PL",
      Model_Complex = "3PL",
      LL_Simple = round(ll_2pl, 2),
      LL_Complex = round(ll_3pl, 2),
      LRT_Statistic = round(lrt_stat, 3),
      df = df_diff,
      p_value = format(p_val, scientific = TRUE, digits = 3),
      Decision = decision,
      Effect_Size = effect_size
    ))
    
    cat("Detailed Results for 2PL vs 3PL:\n")
    cat("2PL Log-likelihood:", round(ll_2pl, 2), "\n")
    cat("3PL Log-likelihood:", round(ll_3pl, 2), "\n")
    cat("Improvement:", round(ll_3pl - ll_2pl, 2), "\n")
    cat("LRT statistic:", round(lrt_stat, 3), "\n")
    cat("Degrees of freedom:", df_diff, "\n")
    cat("p-value:", format(p_val, scientific = TRUE, digits = 3), "\n")
    cat("Pseudo R-squared:", round(pseudo_r2, 4), "\n")
    cat("Decision:", decision, "\n")
    cat("Effect size:", effect_size, "\n\n")
  }
  
  # Display all LRT results
  cat("=== COMPREHENSIVE LRT RESULTS ===\n")
  print(lrt_results)
  
  # LRT interpretation guidelines
  cat("\n=== LRT INTERPRETATION FRAMEWORK ===\n")
  
  lrt_interpretation_framework <- data.frame(
    p_value_range = c("p < 0.001", "0.001 ≤ p < 0.01", "0.01 ≤ p < 0.05", 
                      "0.05 ≤ p < 0.10", "p ≥ 0.10"),
    
    Evidence_Strength = c("Very strong", "Strong", "Moderate", "Weak", "No evidence"),
    
    Statistical_Decision = c("Reject simpler model", "Reject simpler model", "Reject simpler model", 
                            "Marginal evidence", "Accept simpler model"),
    
    Practical_Interpretation = c("Complex model much better", "Complex model clearly better", 
                                "Complex model preferred", "Uncertain - consider other factors", 
                                "Simpler model adequate"),
    
    Recommended_Action = c("Use complex model", "Use complex model", "Use complex model", 
                          "Consider parsimony principle", "Use simpler model"),
    
    Additional_Considerations = c("Check practical significance", "Validate with other criteria", 
                                 "Consider sample size effects", "Look at effect sizes", 
                                 "Prefer parsimony")
  )
  
  print(lrt_interpretation_framework)
  
  # Power and sample size considerations
  cat("\n=== LRT POWER AND SAMPLE SIZE CONSIDERATIONS ===\n")
  
  power_considerations <- c(
    "**Statistical Power in LRT:**",
    "• Large samples: High power to detect small differences",
    "• Small samples: May miss meaningful differences",
    "• Effect size matters: Small improvements may be statistically significant but practically negligible",
    "",
    "**Sample Size Guidelines:**",
    "• n < 200: Use with caution, consider practical significance",
    "• 200 ≤ n < 500: Generally reliable for major model differences",
    "• 500 ≤ n < 1000: Good power for moderate differences",
    "• n ≥ 1000: High power, focus on practical significance",
    "",
    "**Practical Significance Assessment:**",
    "• Pseudo R² < 0.01: Small effect (may not be meaningful)",
    "• 0.01 ≤ Pseudo R² < 0.02: Medium effect",
    "• Pseudo R² ≥ 0.02: Large effect (likely meaningful)",
    "",
    "**Decision Framework:**",
    "1. Check statistical significance (p-value)",
    "2. Assess practical significance (effect size)",
    "3. Consider theoretical justification",
    "4. Evaluate computational/interpretive complexity",
    "5. Make holistic decision"
  )
  
  for(consideration in power_considerations) {
    cat(consideration, "\n")
  }
  
  return(lrt_results)
}

## === LRT POWER AND SAMPLE SIZE CONSIDERATIONS ===
## **Statistical Power in LRT:** 
## • Large samples: High power to detect small differences 
## • Small samples: May miss meaningful differences 
## • Effect size matters: Small improvements may be statistically significant but practically negligible 
##  
## **Sample Size Guidelines:** 
## • n < 200: Use with caution, consider practical significance 
## • 200 ≤ n < 500: Generally reliable for major model differences 
## • 500 ≤ n < 1000: Good power for moderate differences 
## • n ≥ 1000: High power, focus on practical significance 
##  
## **Practical Significance Assessment:** 
## • Pseudo R² < 0.01: Small effect (may not be meaningful) 
## • 0.01 ≤ Pseudo R² < 0.02: Medium effect 
## • Pseudo R² ≥ 0.02: Large effect (likely meaningful) 
##  
## **Decision Framework:** 
## 1. Check statistical significance (p-value) 
## 2. Assess practical significance (effect size) 
## 3. Consider theoretical justification 
## 4. Evaluate computational/interpretive complexity 
## 5. Make holistic decision

# Sequential model building strategy using LRT
sequential_model_building_strategy <- function() {
  
  cat("Sequential Model Building Strategy:\n\n")
  
  strategy_framework <- data.frame(
    Stage = 1:8,
    
    Action = c("Start with baseline model", "Test first extension", "Evaluate results", 
               "Test second extension", "Evaluate results", "Compare all models", 
               "Validate with other criteria", "Make final decision"),
    
    Typical_Sequence = c("1PL (Rasch)", "1PL vs 2PL", "Statistical + practical significance", 
                        "Best of previous vs 3PL", "Statistical + practical significance", 
                        "IC, LRT, fit statistics", "Residuals, assumptions", "Holistic judgment"),
    
    Decision_Rule = c("Establish baseline", "p < 0.05 + meaningful effect", "Consider both p and effect size", 
                      "p < 0.05 + meaningful effect", "Consider both p and effect size", 
                      "Multiple criteria convergence", "Check assumptions", "Best overall model"),
    
    Stopping_Rule = c("Always continue", "Stop if not significant", "Continue if significant", 
                      "Stop if not significant", "Continue if significant", 
                      "Identify best candidate", "Check for violations", "Final choice"),
    
    Common_Pitfalls = c("Wrong baseline", "Ignoring effect size", "P-hacking tendencies", 
                       "Ignoring effect size", "Over-complexifying", "Single criterion focus", 
                       "Ignoring assumptions", "Confirmation bias")
  )
  
  print(strategy_framework)
  
  cat("\nBest Practices for Sequential Building:\n")
  best_practices <- c(
    "• Always start with theoretically justified baseline",
    "• Test one extension at a time (nested comparisons)",
    "• Consider both statistical and practical significance",
    "• Use multiple model fit criteria, not just LRT",
    "• Check model assumptions at each stage",
    "• Document decision rationale clearly",
    "• Consider cross-validation when possible",
    "• Be aware of multiple testing issues"
  )
  
  for(practice in best_practices) {
    cat(practice, "\n")
  }
  
  return(strategy_framework)
}

strategy <- sequential_model_building_strategy()

# Comprehensive residual analysis demonstration
demonstrate_residual_analysis_comprehensive <- function() {
  
  cat("=== COMPREHENSIVE RESIDUAL ANALYSIS DEMONSTRASIYASI ===\n")
  
  # Generate data with some local dependence to create interesting residuals
  set.seed(22222)
  n_persons <- 400
  n_items <- 12
  
  sim_data <- simulate_irt_data_fit(n_persons, n_items, "2PL")
  data_matrix <- sim_data$data
  
  # Introduce systematic patterns for demonstration
  # Local dependence between items 3 and 4
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    if(data_matrix[i, 3] == 1) {
      prob_boost <- rbinom(1, 1, 0.4)  # 40% chance of boost
      if(prob_boost == 1) {
        data_matrix[i, 4] <- 1
      }
    }
  }
  
  # Introduce some differential item functioning (DIF) for items 8-10
  # Create artificial groups
  person_groups <- sample(c("A", "B"), n_persons, replace = TRUE, prob = c(0.6, 0.4))
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    if(person_groups[i] == "B") {
      # Group B has slight advantage on items 8-10
      for(j in 8:10) {
        if(data_matrix[i, j] == 0 && runif(1) < 0.2) {
          data_matrix[i, j] <- 1
        }
      }
    }
  }
  
  cat("Dataset with introduced complexities:\n")
  cat("Persons:", n_persons, "\n")
  cat("Items:", n_items, "\n")
  cat("Patterns introduced:\n")
  cat("• Local dependence between items 3-4\n")
  cat("• Group differences (DIF) for items 8-10\n\n")
  
  # Fit 2PL model
  model_2pl <- mirt(data_matrix, 1, itemtype = "2PL", verbose = FALSE)
  
  # Calculate residuals
  cat("Calculating comprehensive residuals...\n")
  
  # Get residual matrix
  residual_matrix <- residuals(model_2pl, type = "LD")
  
  cat("Residual matrix dimensions:", dim(residual_matrix), "\n\n")
  
  # Comprehensive residual analysis
  cat("=== DETAILED RESIDUAL ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  # 1. Overall residual summary
  all_residuals <- residual_matrix[upper.tri(residual_matrix)]
  
  cat("Overall Residual Summary:\n")
  cat("Mean absolute residual:", round(mean(abs(all_residuals), na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
  cat("SD of residuals:", round(sd(all_residuals, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
  cat("Min residual:", round(min(all_residuals, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
  cat("Max residual:", round(max(all_residuals, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
  
  # 2. Identify large residuals with detailed analysis
  large_residuals <- which(abs(residual_matrix) > 2, arr.ind = TRUE)
  
  cat("\n=== LARGE RESIDUALS (|z| > 2) ===\n")
  
  if(nrow(large_residuals) > 0) {
    
    large_res_detailed <- data.frame(
      Item_i = large_residuals[, 1],
      Item_j = large_residuals[, 2],
      Residual = round(residual_matrix[large_residuals], 3),
      Abs_Residual = round(abs(residual_matrix[large_residuals]), 3),
      Severity = ifelse(abs(residual_matrix[large_residuals]) > 3, "High", "Moderate")
    )
    
    # Sort by absolute residual value
    large_res_detailed <- large_res_detailed[order(-large_res_detailed$Abs_Residual), ]
    
    print(large_res_detailed)
    
    cat("\nInterpretation of Large Residuals:\n")
    cat("• |z| > 2: Potential local dependence or model misfit\n")
    cat("• |z| > 3: Strong evidence of local dependence\n")
    cat("• Expected: Items 3-4 should show large positive residual\n")
    
    # Residual pattern analysis
    cat("\nResidual Pattern Analysis:\n")
    
    # Check for systematic patterns
    high_severity <- sum(large_res_detailed$Severity == "High")
    cat("High severity residuals (|z| > 3):", high_severity, "\n")
    
    # Item involvement analysis
    item_involvement <- table(c(large_res_detailed$Item_i, large_res_detailed$Item_j))
    problematic_items <- names(item_involvement)[item_involvement >= 2]
    
    if(length(problematic_items) > 0) {
      cat("Items involved in multiple large residuals:", paste(problematic_items, collapse = ", "), "\n")
    }
    
  } else {
    cat("No large residuals found (all |z| ≤ 2)\n")
    cat("This suggests good local independence between items\n")
  }
  
  # 3. Visualize residual matrix
  if(require(corrplot, quietly = TRUE)) {
    
    cat("\n=== RESIDUAL VISUALIZATION ===\n")
    
    # Prepare matrix for plotting (remove diagonal)
    plot_matrix <- residual_matrix
    diag(plot_matrix) <- 0
    
    # Create comprehensive heatmap
    corrplot(plot_matrix, 
             method = "color",
             type = "upper",
             order = "original",
             tl.cex = 0.8,
             tl.col = "black",
             title = "Standardized Residuals Matrix",
             mar = c(0,0,2,0),
             col = colorRampPalette(c("blue", "white", "red"))(100),
             is.corr = FALSE)
    
    cat("Residual heatmap interpretation:\n")
    cat("• Red colors: Positive residuals (more responses than expected)\n")
    cat("• Blue colors: Negative residuals (fewer responses than expected)\n")
    cat("• White: Residuals close to zero (good fit)\n\n")
  }
  
  # 4. Item fit statistics (detailed)
  cat("=== COMPREHENSIVE ITEM FIT ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  tryCatch({
    item_fit <- mirt::itemfit(model_2pl)
    
    # Enhanced item fit analysis
    item_fit_enhanced <- data.frame(
      Item = 1:n_items,
      S_X2 = round(item_fit$S_X2, 3),
      df = item_fit$df.S_X2,
      p_value = round(item_fit$p.S_X2, 4),
      Fit_Status = ifelse(item_fit$p.S_X2 < 0.01, "Poor", 
                         ifelse(item_fit$p.S_X2 < 0.05, "Marginal", "Good")),
      RMSEA = round(sqrt(pmax(0, (item_fit$S_X2 - item_fit$df.S_X2) / item_fit$df.S_X2)), 3)
    )
    
    cat("Enhanced Item Fit Summary:\n")
    print(item_fit_enhanced)
    
    # Item fit interpretation
    poor_fit_items <- which(item_fit$p.S_X2 < 0.05)
    marginal_fit_items <- which(item_fit$p.S_X2 >= 0.05 & item_fit$p.S_X2 < 0.10)
    
    cat("\nItem Fit Classification:\n")
    cat("Poor fit items (p < 0.05):", length(poor_fit_items), 
        if(length(poor_fit_items) > 0) paste(" - Items:", paste(poor_fit_items, collapse = ", ")) else "", "\n")
    cat("Marginal fit items (0.05 ≤ p < 0.10):", length(marginal_fit_items),
        if(length(marginal_fit_items) > 0) paste(" - Items:", paste(marginal_fit_items, collapse = ", ")) else "", "\n")
    
    if(length(poor_fit_items) > 0) {
      cat("\nRecommended Actions for Poor-Fitting Items:\n")
      recommendations <- c(
        "• Review item content for clarity and appropriateness",
        "• Check for local dependence with other items",
        "• Consider differential item functioning (DIF)",
        "• Evaluate item discrimination and difficulty parameters",
        "• Consider item revision or removal",
        "• Try alternative IRT models (3PL, testlet models)"
      )
      for(rec in recommendations) {
        cat(rec, "\n")
      }
    }
    
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("Item fit calculation failed:", e$message, "\n")
    poor_fit_items <- numeric(0)
  })
  
  # 5. Person fit statistics (detailed)
  cat("\n=== COMPREHENSIVE PERSON FIT ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  tryCatch({
    person_fit <- mirt::personfit(model_2pl)
    
    # Enhanced person fit analysis
    cat("Person fit summary statistics:\n")
    cat("Mean Zh:", round(mean(person_fit$Zh, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
    cat("SD Zh:", round(sd(person_fit$Zh, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
    cat("Skewness:", round(psych::skew(person_fit$Zh, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
    cat("Kurtosis:", round(psych::kurtosi(person_fit$Zh, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
    
    # Person fit classification
    person_misfit_severe <- sum(abs(person_fit$Zh) > 3, na.rm = TRUE)
    person_misfit_moderate <- sum(abs(person_fit$Zh) > 2 & abs(person_fit$Zh) <= 3, na.rm = TRUE)
    person_misfit_mild <- sum(abs(person_fit$Zh) > 1.5 & abs(person_fit$Zh) <= 2, na.rm = TRUE)
    
    cat("\nPerson Fit Classification:\n")
    cat("Severe misfit (|Zh| > 3):", person_misfit_severe, 
        paste0("(", round(100 * person_misfit_severe / n_persons, 1), "%)"), "\n")
    cat("Moderate misfit (2 < |Zh| ≤ 3):", person_misfit_moderate,
        paste0("(", round(100 * person_misfit_moderate / n_persons, 1), "%)"), "\n")
    cat("Mild misfit (1.5 < |Zh| ≤ 2):", person_misfit_mild,
        paste0("(", round(100 * person_misfit_mild / n_persons, 1), "%)"), "\n")
    
    # Person fit distribution plot
    if(require(ggplot2, quietly = TRUE)) {
      
      person_fit_data <- data.frame(
        Person = 1:length(person_fit$Zh),
        Zh = person_fit$Zh,
        Group = person_groups  # Use the groups we created
      )
      
      p_person_fit <- ggplot(person_fit_data, aes(x = Zh)) +
        geom_histogram(bins = 30, alpha = 0.7, fill = "steelblue", color = "black") +
        geom_vline(xintercept = c(-3, -2, 2, 3), linetype = "dashed", color = "red") +
        labs(title = "Person Fit Distribution (Zh statistic)",
             x = "Zh Statistic", y = "Frequency",
             subtitle = "Dashed lines: ±2 and ±3 thresholds") +
        theme_minimal() +
        theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))
      
      print(p_person_fit)
      
      # Group comparison plot
      p_group_fit <- ggplot(person_fit_data, aes(x = Group, y = Zh, fill = Group)) +
        geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.7) +
        geom_hline(yintercept = c(-2, 2), linetype = "dashed", color = "red") +
        labs(title = "Person Fit by Group",
             x = "Group", y = "Zh Statistic") +
        theme_minimal() +
        theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))
      
      print(p_group_fit)
    }
    
    # Person fit recommendations
    if(person_misfit_severe > n_persons * 0.05) {  # More than 5% severe misfit
      cat("\nPerson Fit Concerns Detected:\n")
      cat("• High rate of person misfit suggests potential issues\n")
      cat("• Consider differential item functioning (DIF) analysis\n")
      cat("• Check for response set bias or careless responding\n")
      cat("• Evaluate model appropriateness for population\n")
    }
    
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("Person fit calculation failed:", e$message, "\n")
    person_misfit_severe <- 0
    person_misfit_moderate <- 0
  })
  
  return(list(
    residuals = residual_matrix,
    item_fit = if(exists("item_fit")) item_fit else NULL,
    person_fit = if(exists("person_fit")) person_fit else NULL,
    large_residuals = if(exists("large_res_detailed")) large_res_detailed else NULL,
    data_used = data_matrix
  ))
}

5 Local Independence Assessment

5.1 Residual Correlation Analysis

cat("=== LOCAL INDEPENDENCE ASSESSMENT ===\n\n")
## === LOCAL INDEPENDENCE ASSESSMENT ===
cat("Local Independence: Items should not be correlated after controlling for ability\n")
## Local Independence: Items should not be correlated after controlling for ability
cat("Method: Residual correlation analysis (Alternative to traditional Q3)\n")
## Method: Residual correlation analysis (Alternative to traditional Q3)
cat("Threshold: |r| > 0.2 indicates potential local dependence\n\n")
## Threshold: |r| > 0.2 indicates potential local dependence
# Comprehensive local independence assessment
demonstrate_local_independence_comprehensive <- function() {
  
  cat("=== COMPREHENSIVE LOCAL INDEPENDENCE ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  # Generate data with known local dependence patterns
  set.seed(33333)
  n_persons <- 600
  n_items <- 10
  
  sim_data <- simulate_irt_data_fit(n_persons, n_items, "2PL")
  data_matrix <- sim_data$data
  
  # Introduce various types of local dependence for demonstration
  cat("Creating diverse local dependence patterns:\n")
  
  # Pattern 1: Items 2-3 (moderate positive dependence)
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    if(data_matrix[i, 2] == 1 && runif(1) < 0.4) {
      data_matrix[i, 3] <- 1
    }
  }
  
  # Pattern 2: Items 7-8 (strong positive dependence)
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    if(data_matrix[i, 7] == 1 && runif(1) < 0.6) {
      data_matrix[i, 8] <- 1
    }
  }
  
  # Pattern 3: Items 5-6 (negative dependence - exclusivity)
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    if(data_matrix[i, 5] == 1 && data_matrix[i, 6] == 1 && runif(1) < 0.3) {
      data_matrix[i, 6] <- 0  # Make them somewhat exclusive
    }
  }
  
  cat("• Items 2-3: Moderate positive dependence\n")
  cat("• Items 7-8: Strong positive dependence\n")
  cat("• Items 5-6: Mild negative dependence (exclusivity)\n\n")
  
  # Fit IRT model
  model_2pl <- mirt(data_matrix, 1, itemtype = "2PL", verbose = FALSE)
  person_abilities <- fscores(model_2pl)[, 1]
  
  cat("Model fitted successfully\n\n")
  
  # Comprehensive residual correlation calculation
  cat("=== ENHANCED RESIDUAL CORRELATION CALCULATION ===\n")
  
  residual_analysis <- calculate_residual_correlations(data_matrix, person_abilities)
  correlation_matrix <- residual_analysis$correlation_matrix
  
  cat("Residual correlation matrix calculated successfully\n\n")
  
  # Comprehensive analysis of correlation matrix
  cat("=== DETAILED CORRELATION ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  # Summary statistics
  upper_tri_indices <- upper.tri(correlation_matrix)
  correlation_values <- correlation_matrix[upper_tri_indices]
  correlation_values <- correlation_values[!is.na(correlation_values)]
  
  cat("Correlation Summary Statistics:\n")
  cat("Total item pairs:", length(correlation_values), "\n")
  cat("Mean absolute correlation:", round(mean(abs(correlation_values)), 3), "\n")
  cat("Median absolute correlation:", round(median(abs(correlation_values)), 3), "\n")
  cat("Max positive correlation:", round(max(correlation_values), 3), "\n")
  cat("Max negative correlation:", round(min(correlation_values), 3), "\n")
  cat("SD of correlations:", round(sd(correlation_values), 3), "\n\n")
  
  # Identify problematic correlations with multiple thresholds
  cat("=== THRESHOLD-BASED CLASSIFICATION ===\n")
  
  # Multiple threshold analysis
  thresholds <- c(0.1, 0.15, 0.2, 0.25, 0.3)
  threshold_results <- data.frame(
    Threshold = thresholds,
    Pairs_Above = sapply(thresholds, function(t) sum(abs(correlation_values) > t)),
    Percentage = sapply(thresholds, function(t) round(100 * sum(abs(correlation_values) > t) / length(correlation_values), 1))
  )
  
  print(threshold_results)
  
  # Detailed analysis for main threshold (0.2)
  high_correlations <- which(abs(correlation_matrix) > 0.2 & upper_tri_indices, arr.ind = TRUE)
  
  cat("\n=== HIGH CORRELATIONS (|r| > 0.2) ===\n")
  
  if(nrow(high_correlations) > 0) {
    
    high_corr_detailed <- data.frame(
      Item_i = high_correlations[, 1],
      Item_j = high_correlations[, 2],
      Correlation = round(correlation_matrix[high_correlations], 3),
      Abs_Correlation = round(abs(correlation_matrix[high_correlations]), 3),
      Direction = ifelse(correlation_matrix[high_correlations] > 0, "Positive", "Negative"),
      Severity = ifelse(abs(correlation_matrix[high_correlations]) > 0.3, "High", 
                       ifelse(abs(correlation_matrix[high_correlations]) > 0.25, "Moderate-High", "Moderate"))
    )
    
    # Sort by absolute correlation
    high_corr_detailed <- high_corr_detailed[order(-high_corr_detailed$Abs_Correlation), ]
    
    print(high_corr_detailed)
    
    cat("\nCorrelation Pattern Analysis:\n")
    
    # Direction analysis
    positive_deps <- sum(high_corr_detailed$Direction == "Positive")
    negative_deps <- sum(high_corr_detailed$Direction == "Negative")
    
    cat("Positive dependencies:", positive_deps, "\n")
    cat("Negative dependencies:", negative_deps, "\n")
    
    # Severity analysis
    severity_table <- table(high_corr_detailed$Severity)
    cat("Severity breakdown:\n")
    print(severity_table)
    
    # Item involvement analysis
    all_items_involved <- c(high_corr_detailed$Item_i, high_corr_detailed$Item_j)
    item_frequency <- table(all_items_involved)
    frequent_items <- names(item_frequency)[item_frequency >= 2]
    
    if(length(frequent_items) > 0) {
      cat("Items involved in multiple dependencies:", paste(frequent_items, collapse = ", "), "\n")
      cat("These items may need special attention\n")
    }
    
    cat("\nExpected Findings Verification:\n")
    cat("• Items 2-3 should show moderate positive correlation\n")
    cat("• Items 7-8 should show strong positive correlation\n")
    cat("• Items 5-6 should show negative correlation\n")
    
  } else {
    cat("No correlations above 0.2 threshold detected\n")
    cat("This suggests good local independence\n")
  }
  
  # Distribution analysis
  cat("\n=== CORRELATION DISTRIBUTION ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  # Create correlation distribution
  correlation_breaks <- c(-1, -0.3, -0.2, -0.1, 0, 0.1, 0.2, 0.3, 1)
  correlation_labels <- c("< -0.3", "-0.3 to -0.2", "-0.2 to -0.1", "-0.1 to 0", 
                         "0 to 0.1", "0.1 to 0.2", "0.2 to 0.3", "> 0.3")
  
  correlation_dist <- table(cut(correlation_values, breaks = correlation_breaks, labels = correlation_labels))
  
  cat("Correlation Distribution:\n")
  print(correlation_dist)
  
  # Expected distribution analysis
  cat("\nDistribution Analysis:\n")
  near_zero <- sum(abs(correlation_values) < 0.1)
  cat("Correlations near zero (|r| < 0.1):", near_zero, 
      paste0("(", round(100 * near_zero / length(correlation_values), 1), "%)"), "\n")
  
  # Visualization
  if(require(corrplot, quietly = TRUE)) {
    
    cat("\n=== CORRELATION VISUALIZATION ===\n")
    
    # Prepare matrix for plotting
    plot_matrix <- correlation_matrix
    diag(plot_matrix) <- NA
    
    # Enhanced correlation plot
    corrplot(plot_matrix, 
             method = "color",
             type = "upper",
             order = "original",
             tl.cex = 0.8,
             tl.col = "black",
             title = "Residual Correlations Matrix",
             mar = c(0,0,2,0),
             col = colorRampPalette(c("blue", "white", "red"))(100),
             na.label = " ",
             na.label.col = "white")
    
    cat("Visualization completed\n")
    cat("Red: Positive correlations (local dependence)\n")
    cat("Blue: Negative correlations (exclusivity/redundancy)\n")
    cat("White: Near-zero correlations (independence)\n\n")
  }
  
  # Advanced pattern detection
  cat("=== ADVANCED PATTERN DETECTION ===\n")
  
  # Cluster analysis of highly correlated items
  if(nrow(high_correlations) > 0) {
    
    # Create adjacency matrix for network analysis
    adjacency_matrix <- matrix(0, n_items, n_items)
    for(i in 1:nrow(high_correlations)) {
      row_idx <- high_correlations[i, 1]
      col_idx <- high_correlations[i, 2]
      adjacency_matrix[row_idx, col_idx] <- 1
      adjacency_matrix[col_idx, row_idx] <- 1  # Symmetric
    }
    
    # Find connected components (clusters of dependent items)
    diag(adjacency_matrix) <- 1  # Each item connected to itself
    
    # Simple cluster detection
    clusters <- list()
    remaining_items <- 1:n_items
    cluster_id <- 1
    
    while(length(remaining_items) > 0) {
      current_item <- remaining_items[1]
      current_cluster <- current_item
      
      # Find all items connected to current item
      to_check <- current_item
      while(length(to_check) > 0) {
        checking_item <- to_check[1]
        to_check <- to_check[-1]
        
        connected_items <- which(adjacency_matrix[checking_item, ] == 1)
        new_items <- setdiff(connected_items, current_cluster)
        
        if(length(new_items) > 0) {
          current_cluster <- c(current_cluster, new_items)
          to_check <- c(to_check, new_items)
        }
      }
      
      if(length(current_cluster) > 1) {  # Only report clusters with multiple items
        clusters[[cluster_id]] <- sort(current_cluster)
        cluster_id <- cluster_id + 1
      }
      
      remaining_items <- setdiff(remaining_items, current_cluster)
    }
    
    if(length(clusters) > 0) {
      cat("Detected Item Clusters (locally dependent groups):\n")
      for(i in 1:length(clusters)) {
        cat("Cluster", i, ": Items", paste(clusters[[i]], collapse = ", "), "\n")
      }
      
      cat("\nCluster Analysis Implications:\n")
      cat("• Consider testlet models for clustered items\n")
      cat("• Evaluate possibility of multidimensional structure\n")
      cat("• Review item content for shared specific factors\n")
    } else {
      cat("No clear item clusters detected\n")
    }
  }
  
  # Recommendations based on local independence analysis
  cat("\n=== RECOMMENDATIONS BASED ON LOCAL INDEPENDENCE ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  if(exists("high_corr_detailed") && nrow(high_corr_detailed) > 0) {
    
    recommendation_categories <- c(
      "**IMMEDIATE ACTIONS:**",
      "• Review content of highly correlated item pairs",
      "• Check for shared specific factors or response dependencies",
      "• Consider combining dependent items into testlets",
      "",
      "**MODELING APPROACHES:**",
      "• Test bifactor models if many dependencies detected",
      "• Consider multidimensional IRT models",
      "• Explore testlet response theory models",
      "• Investigate locally dependent item response models",
      "",
      "**CONTENT REVIEW:**",
      "• Examine items for shared context or stimulus",
      "• Check for similar wording or content overlap",
      "• Review for sequential dependencies",
      "• Assess cognitive processing similarities",
      "",
      "**QUALITY IMPROVEMENT:**",
      paste("• Prioritize revision of items with |r| >", max(high_corr_detailed$Abs_Correlation)),
      "• Consider removing one item from highly dependent pairs",
      "• Develop alternative items to reduce dependencies",
      "• Implement systematic item review procedures"
    )
    
  } else {
    
    recommendation_categories <- c(
      "**POSITIVE FINDINGS:**",
      "• No significant local dependence detected",
      "• Unidimensional IRT model assumptions appear satisfied",
      "• Items demonstrate good local independence",
      "• Current model structure appears appropriate",
      "",
      "**ONGOING MONITORING:**",
      "• Continue to monitor in future administrations",
      "• Include local independence checks in routine QC",
      "• Watch for changes with different populations",
      "• Maintain documentation of independence validation"
    )
  }
  
  for(rec in recommendation_categories) {
    cat(rec, "\n")
  }
  
  return(list(
    correlation_matrix = correlation_matrix,
    high_correlations = if(exists("high_corr_detailed")) high_corr_detailed else NULL,
    correlation_values = correlation_values,
    clusters = if(exists("clusters")) clusters else NULL
  ))
}

# Run comprehensive local independence analysis
local_independence_comprehensive_results <- demonstrate_local_independence_comprehensive()

6 Bootstrap Parameter Stability

6.1 Comprehensive Parameter Stability Assessment

cat("=== BOOTSTRAP PARAMETER STABILITY ANALYSIS ===\n\n")
## === BOOTSTRAP PARAMETER STABILITY ANALYSIS ===
cat("Bootstrap Method: Resampling-based assessment of parameter stability\n")
## Bootstrap Method: Resampling-based assessment of parameter stability
cat("Goal: Quantify parameter estimation uncertainty and validate reliability\n")
## Goal: Quantify parameter estimation uncertainty and validate reliability
cat("Metrics: Bias, standard errors, confidence intervals, stability coefficients\n\n")
## Metrics: Bias, standard errors, confidence intervals, stability coefficients
# Comprehensive bootstrap analysis
demonstrate_bootstrap_comprehensive <- function() {
  
  cat("=== COMPREHENSIVE BOOTSTRAP ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  # Generate stable dataset for demonstration
  set.seed(44444)
  n_persons <- 300
  n_items <- 8
  
  sim_data <- simulate_irt_data_fit(n_persons, n_items, "2PL")
  data_matrix <- sim_data$data
  true_params <- sim_data$true_params
  
  cat("Dataset for bootstrap analysis:\n")
  cat("Persons:", n_persons, "\n")
  cat("Items:", n_items, "\n")
  cat("Model: 2PL\n\n")
  
  # Original model estimation
  cat("Fitting original model...\n")
  original_model <- mirt(data_matrix, 1, itemtype = "2PL", verbose = FALSE)
  original_params <- coef(original_model, simplify = TRUE)
  
  # Extract original parameters
  orig_discrimination <- original_params$items[, "a1"]
  orig_difficulty <- original_params$items[, "d"] / (-original_params$items[, "a1"])
  
  cat("Original model fitted successfully\n\n")
  
  # Comprehensive bootstrap analysis
  cat("Running comprehensive bootstrap analysis...\n")
  
  n_bootstrap <- 100  # Increased for better estimates
  bootstrap_results <- bootstrap_irt_parameters(data_matrix, "2PL", n_bootstrap)
  
  # Extract successful bootstrap samples
  successful_boots <- !is.na(bootstrap_results$aic)
  n_successful <- sum(successful_boots)
  
  cat("Bootstrap completed:\n")
  cat("Total bootstrap samples:", n_bootstrap, "\n")
  cat("Successful estimations:", n_successful, "\n")
  cat("Success rate:", round(100 * n_successful / n_bootstrap, 1), "%\n\n")
  
  if(n_successful >= 20) {  # Need adequate successful samples
    
    # Extract successful parameters
    boot_disc <- bootstrap_results$parameters[successful_boots, , 1]
    boot_diff <- bootstrap_results$parameters[successful_boots, , 2]
    
    # Remove any remaining NA rows
    complete_rows <- complete.cases(boot_disc) & complete.cases(boot_diff)
    boot_disc <- boot_disc[complete_rows, ]
    boot_diff <- boot_diff[complete_rows, ]
    n_complete <- sum(complete_rows)
    
    cat("Complete bootstrap samples used:", n_complete, "\n\n")
    
    if(n_complete >= 10) {
      
      # Comprehensive parameter stability analysis
      cat("=== DETAILED PARAMETER STABILITY ANALYSIS ===\n")
      
      # Calculate comprehensive statistics
      stability_detailed <- data.frame(
        Item = 1:n_items,
        
        # True parameters
        True_Discrimination = round(true_params$discriminations, 3),
        True_Difficulty = round(true_params$difficulties, 3),
        
        # Original estimates
        Original_Discrimination = round(orig_discrimination, 3),
        Original_Difficulty = round(orig_difficulty, 3),
        
        # Bootstrap means
        Boot_Mean_Discrimination = round(colMeans(boot_disc, na.rm = TRUE), 3),
        Boot_Mean_Difficulty = round(colMeans(boot_diff, na.rm = TRUE), 3),
        
        # Bootstrap standard errors
        Boot_SE_Discrimination = round(apply(boot_disc, 2, sd, na.rm = TRUE), 3),
        Boot_SE_Difficulty = round(apply(boot_diff, 2, sd, na.rm = TRUE), 3),
        
        # Bias (bootstrap mean - original)
        Bias_Discrimination = round(colMeans(boot_disc, na.rm = TRUE) - orig_discrimination, 3),
        Bias_Difficulty = round(colMeans(boot_diff, na.rm = TRUE) - orig_difficulty, 3),
        
        # Relative standard errors
        Relative_SE_Discrimination = round(apply(boot_disc, 2, sd, na.rm = TRUE) / abs(orig_discrimination), 3),
        Relative_SE_Difficulty = round(apply(boot_diff, 2, sd, na.rm = TRUE) / abs(orig_difficulty), 3)
      )
      
      cat("Comprehensive Parameter Stability Summary:\n")
      print(stability_detailed)
      
      # Overall stability assessment
      cat("\n=== OVERALL STABILITY ASSESSMENT ===\n")
      
      # Calculate summary statistics
      mean_bias_disc <- mean(abs(stability_detailed$Bias_Discrimination), na.rm = TRUE)
      mean_bias_diff <- mean(abs(stability_detailed$Bias_Difficulty), na.rm = TRUE)
      
      mean_relative_se_disc <- mean(stability_detailed$Relative_SE_Discrimination, na.rm = TRUE)
      mean_relative_se_diff <- mean(stability_detailed$Relative_SE_Difficulty, na.rm = TRUE)
      
      # Parameter recovery correlations
      recovery_corr_disc <- cor(true_params$discriminations, colMeans(boot_disc, na.rm = TRUE))
      recovery_corr_diff <- cor(true_params$difficulties, colMeans(boot_diff, na.rm = TRUE))
      
      cat("Summary Statistics:\n")
      cat("Mean absolute bias - Discrimination:", round(mean_bias_disc, 3), "\n")
      cat("Mean absolute bias - Difficulty:", round(mean_bias_diff, 3), "\n")
      cat("Mean relative SE - Discrimination:", round(mean_relative_se_disc, 3), "\n")
      cat("Mean relative SE - Difficulty:", round(mean_relative_se_diff, 3), "\n")
      cat("Parameter recovery correlation - Discrimination:", round(recovery_corr_disc, 3), "\n")
      cat("Parameter recovery correlation - Difficulty:", round(recovery_corr_diff, 3), "\n\n")
      
      # Stability classification
      stability_classification <- function(rel_se) {
        ifelse(rel_se < 0.05, "Excellent", 
               ifelse(rel_se < 0.10, "Very Good",
                      ifelse(rel_se < 0.15, "Good",
                             ifelse(rel_se < 0.20, "Acceptable", "Poor"))))
      }
      
      disc_stability_class <- stability_classification(mean_relative_se_disc)
      diff_stability_class <- stability_classification(mean_relative_se_diff)
      
      cat("Overall Stability Classification:\n")
      cat("Discrimination parameters:", disc_stability_class, "\n")
      cat("Difficulty parameters:", diff_stability_class, "\n\n")
      
      # Bootstrap confidence intervals
      cat("=== BOOTSTRAP CONFIDENCE INTERVALS ===\n")
      
      confidence_level <- 0.95
      alpha <- 1 - confidence_level
      
      ci_detailed <- data.frame(
        Item = 1:n_items,
        
        # Discrimination CIs
        Disc_Original = round(orig_discrimination, 3),
        Disc_CI_Lower = round(apply(boot_disc, 2, quantile, alpha/2, na.rm = TRUE), 3),
        Disc_CI_Upper = round(apply(boot_disc, 2, quantile, 1-alpha/2, na.rm = TRUE), 3),
        Disc_CI_Width = round(apply(boot_disc, 2, quantile, 1-alpha/2, na.rm = TRUE) - 
                             apply(boot_disc, 2, quantile, alpha/2, na.rm = TRUE), 3),
        
        # Difficulty CIs
        Diff_Original = round(orig_difficulty, 3),
        Diff_CI_Lower = round(apply(boot_diff, 2, quantile, alpha/2, na.rm = TRUE), 3),
        Diff_CI_Upper = round(apply(boot_diff, 2, quantile, 1-alpha/2, na.rm = TRUE), 3),
        Diff_CI_Width = round(apply(boot_diff, 2, quantile, 1-alpha/2, na.rm = TRUE) - 
                             apply(boot_diff, 2, quantile, alpha/2, na.rm = TRUE), 3)
      )
      
      cat("95% Bootstrap Confidence Intervals:\n")
      print(ci_detailed)
      
      # Coverage assessment (how often true parameters fall within CIs)
      cat("\n=== COVERAGE ASSESSMENT ===\n")
      
      disc_coverage <- (true_params$discriminations >= ci_detailed$Disc_CI_Lower & 
                        true_params$discriminations <= ci_detailed$Disc_CI_Upper)
      diff_coverage <- (true_params$difficulties >= ci_detailed$Diff_CI_Lower & 
                        true_params$difficulties <= ci_detailed$Diff_CI_Upper)
      
      coverage_summary <- data.frame(
        Item = 1:n_items,
        True_Discrimination = round(true_params$discriminations, 3),
        Disc_Covered = disc_coverage,
        True_Difficulty = round(true_params$difficulties, 3),
        Diff_Covered = diff_coverage
      )
      
      print(coverage_summary)
      
      cat("\nCoverage Performance:\n")
      cat("Discrimination coverage rate:", round(100 * mean(disc_coverage), 1), "%\n")
      cat("Difficulty coverage rate:", round(100 * mean(diff_coverage), 1), "%\n")
      cat("Expected coverage (95% CI):", round(100 * confidence_level, 1), "%\n")
      
      # Coverage interpretation
      if(mean(disc_coverage) >= 0.90 && mean(diff_coverage) >= 0.90) {
        cat("Coverage assessment: EXCELLENT - CIs performing as expected\n")
      } else if(mean(disc_coverage) >= 0.80 && mean(diff_coverage) >= 0.80) {
        cat("Coverage assessment: GOOD - CIs reasonably accurate\n")
      } else {
        cat("Coverage assessment: POOR - CIs may be unreliable\n")
      }
      
      # Visualize bootstrap distributions for selected items
      if(require(ggplot2, quietly = TRUE)) {
        
        cat("\n=== BOOTSTRAP DISTRIBUTION VISUALIZATION ===\n")
        
        # Prepare data for plotting (first 4 items)
        plot_items <- min(4, n_items)
        
        plot_data_disc <- data.frame()
        plot_data_diff <- data.frame()
        
        for(i in 1:plot_items) {
          item_data_disc <- data.frame(
            Item = paste("Item", i),
            Value = boot_disc[, i],
            True_Value = true_params$discriminations[i],
            Original_Value = orig_discrimination[i],
            Parameter = "Discrimination"
          )
          plot_data_disc <- rbind(plot_data_disc, item_data_disc)
          
          item_data_diff <- data.frame(
            Item = paste("Item", i),
            Value = boot_diff[, i],
            True_Value = true_params$difficulties[i],
            Original_Value = orig_difficulty[i],
            Parameter = "Difficulty"
          )
          plot_data_diff <- rbind(plot_data_diff, item_data_diff)
        }
        
        plot_data_combined <- rbind(plot_data_disc, plot_data_diff)
        
        # Create comprehensive bootstrap plot
        p_bootstrap <- ggplot(plot_data_combined, aes(x = Value)) +
          geom_histogram(aes(y = ..density..), bins = 15, alpha = 0.7, fill = "skyblue", color = "black") +
          geom_vline(aes(xintercept = True_Value), color = "red", linetype = "solid", size = 1) +
          geom_vline(aes(xintercept = Original_Value), color = "blue", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) +
          facet_grid(Parameter ~ Item, scales = "free") +
          labs(title = "Bootstrap Parameter Distributions",
               subtitle = "Red line: True value, Blue dashed: Original estimate",
               x = "Parameter Value", y = "Density") +
          theme_minimal() +
          theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 14, face = "bold"),
                plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 12),
                strip.text = element_text(size = 10, face = "bold"))
        
        print(p_bootstrap)
        
        cat("Bootstrap distribution visualization completed\n\n")
      }
      
      # Parameter stability over bootstrap iterations
      cat("=== PARAMETER STABILITY OVER ITERATIONS ===\n")
      
      # Calculate cumulative means to assess convergence
      cumulative_means_disc <- apply(boot_disc, 2, function(x) cumsum(x) / seq_along(x))
      cumulative_means_diff <- apply(boot_diff, 2, function(x) cumsum(x) / seq_along(x))
      
      # Check convergence for first item as example
      if(n_complete >= 20) {
        final_10_pct <- max(1, floor(n_complete * 0.9)):n_complete
        stability_disc_1 <- sd(cumulative_means_disc[final_10_pct, 1]) / mean(cumulative_means_disc[final_10_pct, 1])
        stability_diff_1 <- sd(cumulative_means_diff[final_10_pct, 1]) / mean(cumulative_means_diff[final_10_pct, 1])
        
        cat("Convergence assessment (Item 1):\n")
        cat("Discrimination stability (final 10%):", round(stability_disc_1, 4), "\n")
        cat("Difficulty stability (final 10%):", round(stability_diff_1, 4), "\n")
        
        if(stability_disc_1 < 0.01 && stability_diff_1 < 0.01) {
          cat("Convergence status: EXCELLENT - Very stable estimates\n")
        } else if(stability_disc_1 < 0.02 && stability_diff_1 < 0.02) {
          cat("Convergence status: GOOD - Reasonably stable estimates\n")
        } else {
          cat("Convergence status: POOR - May need more bootstrap samples\n")
        }
      }
      
    } else {
      cat("Insufficient complete bootstrap samples for detailed analysis\n")
    }
    
  } else {
    cat("Insufficient successful bootstrap samples for analysis\n")
    cat("Consider:\n")
    cat("• Increasing sample size\n")
    cat("• Simplifying model\n")
    cat("• Checking data quality\n")
  }
  
  # Model fit stability analysis
  cat("\n=== MODEL FIT STABILITY ANALYSIS ===\n")
  
  if(sum(successful_boots) > 0) {
    
    boot_loglik_clean <- bootstrap_results$loglik[successful_boots & !is.na(bootstrap_results$loglik)]
    boot_aic_clean <- bootstrap_results$aic[successful_boots & !is.na(bootstrap_results$aic)]
    
    original_loglik <- extract.mirt(original_model, "logLik")
    original_aic <- extract.mirt(original_model, "AIC")
    
    if(length(boot_loglik_clean) > 5) {
      
      fit_stability_detailed <- data.frame(
        Statistic = c("Log-likelihood", "AIC"),
        Original = round(c(original_loglik, original_aic), 2),
        Boot_Mean = round(c(mean(boot_loglik_clean, na.rm = TRUE), mean(boot_aic_clean, na.rm = TRUE)), 2),
        Boot_SE = round(c(sd(boot_loglik_clean, na.rm = TRUE), sd(boot_aic_clean, na.rm = TRUE)), 2),
        Boot_CV = round(c(sd(boot_loglik_clean, na.rm = TRUE) / abs(mean(boot_loglik_clean, na.rm = TRUE)),
                         sd(boot_aic_clean, na.rm = TRUE) / abs(mean(boot_aic_clean, na.rm = TRUE))), 4),
        Boot_Range = paste(round(c(min(boot_loglik_clean, na.rm = TRUE), min(boot_aic_clean, na.rm = TRUE)), 2), 
                          "to",
                          round(c(max(boot_loglik_clean, na.rm = TRUE), max(boot_aic_clean, na.rm = TRUE)), 2))
      )
      
      print(fit_stability_detailed)
      
      cat("\nModel Fit Stability Assessment:\n")
      
      loglik_cv <- sd(boot_loglik_clean, na.rm = TRUE) / abs(mean(boot_loglik_clean, na.rm = TRUE))
      aic_cv <- sd(boot_aic_clean, na.rm = TRUE) / abs(mean(boot_aic_clean, na.rm = TRUE))
      
      cat("Log-likelihood CV:", round(loglik_cv, 4), "\n")
      cat("AIC CV:", round(aic_cv, 4), "\n")
      
      if(loglik_cv < 0.005 && aic_cv < 0.005) {
        cat("Model fit stability: EXCELLENT - Very consistent across samples\n")
      } else if(loglik_cv < 0.01 && aic_cv < 0.01) {
        cat("Model fit stability: GOOD - Reasonably consistent\n")
      } else if(loglik_cv < 0.02 && aic_cv < 0.02) {
        cat("Model fit stability: ACCEPTABLE - Some variation present\n")
      } else {
        cat("Model fit stability: POOR - High variation across samples\n")
      }
    }
  }
  
  return(list(
    original_params = list(discrimination = orig_discrimination, difficulty = orig_difficulty),
    bootstrap_results = bootstrap_results,
    stability_summary = if(exists("stability_detailed")) stability_detailed else NULL,
    coverage_summary = if(exists("coverage_summary")) coverage_summary else NULL
  ))
}
